##
## Introduction
##
@node introduction Introduction

    'R3Version' is a version reporting tool for 'Real3d' [(c)RealSoft] users.
    To my knowledge it should work with any 'Real3d' version, this due to the
    fact that these clever guys used the IFF format.

    Its purpose is to have a quick way of determining the version of 'Real3d'
    data files without starting up 'Real3d'.

    Bonus Usage: from version 1.1 a full IFF chunk scanner is present, it works
                  on ALL IFF structured files.
                  
                      
    The program will report the following 'Real3D' filetypes:    objects,
                                                                 materials,
                                                                 projects.
    
    Additionally it will "recognize" following IFF chunks, allowing for version
    reporting on following specific 'Real3D' types: 

                - RWIN    windows descriptions
                - RSTT    global settings
                - RSCR    screens
                - RCOL    predefined colors
                - RINF    measuring system
                - RANI    animation settings
                - RREN    render settings
                - RGRI    grid settings
                - RRPL    RPL command files
                - RCMD    command hunk.
            
    
@endnode

##
## Usage
##
@node usage Usage

    
    R3Version uses standard AmigaDOS command patterns, and typing 'R3VERSION ?' 
    will give,
    
                        FILE/A,ALL/S,VERBOSE/S,VAR=/K,GLOBAL/S,QUIET/S
                        
    where:
    
                FILE/A        - the file to examine
                ALL/S         - list all information in the 'RVRS' chunk
                VERBOSE/S     - list structure of ANY Iff file (IFF SCAN)
                VAR=/K        - the variable name to store the version
                GLOBAL/S      - make variable global (otherwise LOCAL)
                QUIET/S       - no output to CLI.
    
    It is evident that using 'QUIET' with 'ALL/VERBOSE' is illegal since it is
    the purpose of this functions to list data.
    
    Also, it is illegal to use 'VAR' with 'ALL/VERBOSE'.

    Additionally typing 'R3VERSION ??' will give above explanation in the CLI
    session.
    
    
    Examples:
    
    
        1>r3version objects/face
        2.47
        1>
        
        
        1>r3version materials/mylib var=matv global
        1>getenv matv
        2.47
        1>
        
        
        1>r3version all objects/face
        Version     : 2.47
        Platform    : AMIG
        Byteorder   :    0 (0=Amiga, 1=Intel)
        1>
        
                 
        1>r3version verbose objects/face
        - FORM 72894 REAL
        - - RVRS 12 REAL
        - - ROBJ 72862 REAL
        Ended.
        1>
            
        
        1>r3version work:data/pics/iff/vid10.iff
        - FORM 107428 ILBM
        - - BMHD 20 ILBM
        - - ANNO 68 ILBM
        - - CAMG 4 ILBM
        - - CMAP 48 ILBM
        - - BODY 107243 ILBM
        Ended.
        1>
                                                    
@endnode
